  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Upon Visiting Jikgyeong and Expressing My Feelings in Verse
  author: Park Eun
  language: eng
  text: |
    This old man—no one loves him,
    yet still his body wrestles with disease.
    Half a year spent lying down,
    his withered bones a sight to startle.

    Before I came, I fretted needlessly,
    but meeting him, his eyes still gleamed.
    Over a cup of wine we spoke of hearts,
    and on my way home, night grew deep.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Jikgyeong (直卿) was likely the poet's friend or acquaintance, addressed by an affectionate or respectful epithet.
  - key: ''
    value: The contrast between the speaker's worry before the visit and the comfort found in the friend's still-bright eyes emphasizes the power of human connection to transcend physical decline.
